AddLink
TCPDF::AddLink() in tcpdf.php
Creates a new internal link and returns its identifier. An internal link is a clickable area which directs to another place within the document.
The identifier can then be passed to Cell(), Write(), Image() or Link(). The destination is defined with SetLink().
addMeta

AddPage
TCPDF::AddPage() in tcpdf.php
Adds a new page to the document. If a page is already present, the Footer() method is called first to output the footer (if enabled). Then the page is added, the current position set to the top-left corner according to the left and top margins (or top-right if in RTL mode), and Header() is called to display the header (if enabled).

Cell
TCPDF::Cell() in tcpdf.php
Prints a cell (rectangular area) with optional borders, background color and character string. The upper-left corner of the cell corresponds to the current position. The text can be aligned or centered. After the call, the current position moves to the right or to the next line. It is possible to put a link on the text.
If automatic page breaking is enabled and the cell goes beyond the limit, a page break is done before outputting.

decodeFilter
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilter() in tcpdf_filters.php
Decode data using the specified filter type.
decodeFilterASCII85Decode
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterASCII85Decode() in tcpdf_filters.php
ASCII85Decode Decodes data encoded in an ASCII base-85 representation, reproducing the original binary data.
decodeFilterASCIIHexDecode
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterASCIIHexDecode() in tcpdf_filters.php
ASCIIHexDecode Decodes data encoded in an ASCII hexadecimal representation, reproducing the original binary data.
decodeFilterCCITTFaxDecode
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterCCITTFaxDecode() in tcpdf_filters.php
CCITTFaxDecode (NOT IMPLEMETED) Decompresses data encoded using the CCITT facsimile standard, reproducing the original data (typically monochrome image data at 1 bit per pixel).
decodeFilterCrypt
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterCrypt() in tcpdf_filters.php
Crypt (NOT IMPLEMETED) Decrypts data encrypted by a security handler, reproducing the data as it was before encryption.
decodeFilterDCTDecode
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterDCTDecode() in tcpdf_filters.php
DCTDecode (NOT IMPLEMETED) Decompresses data encoded using a DCT (discrete cosine transform) technique based on the JPEG standard, reproducing image sample data that approximates the original data.
decodeFilterFlateDecode
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterFlateDecode() in tcpdf_filters.php
FlateDecode Decompresses data encoded using the zlib/deflate compression method, reproducing the original text or binary data.
decodeFilterJBIG2Decode
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterJBIG2Decode() in tcpdf_filters.php
JBIG2Decode (NOT IMPLEMETED) Decompresses data encoded using the JBIG2 standard, reproducing the original monochrome (1 bit per pixel) image data (or an approximation of that data).
decodeFilterJPXDecode
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterJPXDecode() in tcpdf_filters.php
JPXDecode (NOT IMPLEMETED) Decompresses data encoded using the wavelet-based JPEG2000 standard, reproducing the original image data.
decodeFilterLZWDecode
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterLZWDecode() in tcpdf_filters.php
LZWDecode Decompresses data encoded using the LZW (Lempel-Ziv-Welch) adaptive compression method, reproducing the original text or binary data.
decodeFilterRunLengthDecode
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterRunLengthDecode() in tcpdf_filters.php
RunLengthDecode Decompresses data encoded using a byte-oriented run-length encoding algorithm.
decodeFilterStandard
TCPDF_FILTERS::decodeFilterStandard() in tcpdf_filters.php
Standard Default decoding filter (leaves data unchanged).

getCellBorder

getCellCode
TCPDF::getCellCode() in tcpdf.php
Returns the PDF string code to print a cell (rectangular area) with optional borders, background color and character string. The upper-left corner of the cell corresponds to the current position. The text can be aligned or centered. After the call, the current position moves to the right or to the next line. It is possible to put a link on the text.
If automatic page breaking is enabled and the cell goes beyond the limit, a page break is done before outputting.

QR_MODE_AN in qrcode.php
Encoding mode alphanumeric (0-9A-Z $%*+-./:) 45characters. 2 characters are encoded to 11bit length. In theory, 4296 characters or less can be stored in a QRcode.

QR_MODE_KJ in qrcode.php
Encoding mode KANJI. A KANJI character (multibyte character) is encoded to 13bit length. In theory, 1817 characters or less can be stored in a QRcode.
